Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with simultaneous wireless information and power transfer, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of different receiver architectures and transmission signal designs, which are important aspects of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves the design and analysis of a practical SWIPT system, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper evaluates the performance of different modulation schemes, which is a topic related to multimedia. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper involves the implementation of a realistic SWIPT prototype, which falls under the domain of hardware architecture.
